    "For function types 2 through 4, the GDOT data dictionary says digits 6 through 8 are reference post and digits 9 through 11 are the underlying route number.",
    "For public-road mainline route IDs, suffix 00 is treated as county road and numeric suffixes 01 through 99 are treated as city street using GDOT route-guide examples.",
    "U.S. Route classifications remain medium-confidence because Georgia route IDs encode state route numbers, so concurrency and hidden-route cases can still exist."
